\end{equation}

Thus, we have:
\begin{equation}
    E_y = \mu_0 v H_x \tag{4}
\end{equation}

Using the relation $v = \frac{1}{\sqrt{\mu_0 \varepsilon_0}}$, we can rewrite equation (4) in the form:
\begin{equation}
    E_y = Z_0 H_x
\end{equation}
